  "lesson_body": "When implementing a custom deep-copy protocol for an object that owns auxiliary helpers or sub-proxies, each helper must be reconstructed bound to the NEW object — not the original. Failing to rebind causes the copy's helpers to silently share state with the source, so mutations on one leak into the other.",
